{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|Jer|8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","chapter":8,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v10","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:8:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":8,"verse":1,"text":"“At that time” —this is the Lord’s declaration —“the bones of the kings of Judah, the bones of her officials, the bones of the priests, the bones of the prophets, and the bones of the residents of Jerusalem will be brought out of their graves.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:8:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":8,"verse":2,"text":"They will be exposed to the sun, the moon, and all the stars in the sky, which they have loved, served, followed, consulted, and worshiped. Their bones will not be collected and buried but will become like manure on the soil’s surface.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:8:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":8,"verse":3,"text":"Death will be chosen over life by all the survivors of this evil family, those who remain wherever I have banished them.” This is the declaration of the Lord of Armies.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:8:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":8,"verse":4,"text":"“You are to say to them: This is what the Lord says:","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:8:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":8,"verse":5,"text":"Why have these people turned away?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:8:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":8,"verse":6,"text":"I have paid careful attention.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:8:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":8,"verse":7,"text":"Even storks in the sky","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:8:8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":8,"verse":8,"text":"“How can you claim, ‘We are wise;","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:8:9","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":8,"verse":9,"text":"The wise will be put to shame;","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:8:10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":8,"verse":10,"text":"Therefore, I will give their wives to other men,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:8:11","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":8,"verse":11,"text":"They have treated the brokenness","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:8:12","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":8,"verse":12,"text":"Were they ashamed when they acted so detestably?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:8:13","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":8,"verse":13,"text":"“I will gather them and bring them to an end.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:8:14","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":8,"verse":14,"text":"Why are we just sitting here?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:8:15","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":8,"verse":15,"text":"We hoped for peace, but there was nothing good;","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:8:16","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":